 1089        void SafeGetInstances(ProviderInfo providerInfo, InjectContext context, List<object> instances)
 01090        {
 01091            Assert.IsNotNull(context);
 1092
 01093            var provider = providerInfo.Provider;
 1094
 01095            if (ChecksForCircularDependencies)
 01096            {
 01097                var lookupId = ZenPools.SpawnLookupId(provider, context.BindingId);
 1098
 1099                try
 01100                {
 1101                    // Use the container associated with the provider to address some rare cases
 1102                    // which would otherwise result in an infinite loop.  Like this:
 1103                    // Container.Bind<ICharacter>().FromComponentInNewPrefab(Prefab).AsTransient()
 1104                    // With the prefab being a GameObjectContext containing a script that has a
 1105                    // ICharacter dependency.  In this case, we would otherwise use the _resolvesInProgress
 1106                    // associated with the GameObjectContext container, which will allow the recursive
 1107                    // lookup, which will trigger another GameObjectContext and container (since it is
 1108                    // transient) and the process continues indefinitely
 01109                    var providerContainer = providerInfo.Container;
 1110
 01111                    if (providerContainer._resolvesTwiceInProgress.Contains(lookupId))
 01112                    {
 1113                        // Allow one before giving up so that you can do circular dependencies via postinject or fields
 01114                        throw Assert.CreateException(
 1115                            "Circular dependency detected! Object graph:\n {0}", context.GetObjectGraphString());
 1116                    }
 1117
 01118                    bool twice = false;
 01119                    if (!providerContainer._resolvesInProgress.Add(lookupId))
 01120                    {
 01121                        bool added = providerContainer._resolvesTwiceInProgress.Add(lookupId);
 01122                        Assert.That(added);
 01123                        twice = true;
 01124                    }
 1125
 1126                    try
 01127                    {
 01128                        GetDecoratedInstances(provider, context, instances);
 01129                    }
 1130                    finally
 01131                    {
 01132                        if (twice)
 01133                        {
 01134                            bool removed = providerContainer._resolvesTwiceInProgress.Remove(lookupId);
 01135                            Assert.That(removed);
 01136                        }
 1137                        else
 01138                        {
 01139                            bool removed = providerContainer._resolvesInProgress.Remove(lookupId);
 01140                            Assert.That(removed);
 01141                        }
 01142                    }
 01143                }
 1144                finally
 01145                {
 01146                    ZenPools.DespawnLookupId(lookupId);
 01147                }
 01148            }
 1149            else
 01150            {
 01151                GetDecoratedInstances(provider, context, instances);
 01152            }
 01153        }

 1426        public void InjectExplicit(
 1427            object injectable, Type injectableType,
 1428            List<TypeValuePair> extraArgs, InjectContext context, object concreteIdentifier)
 01429        {
 1430#if ZEN_INTERNAL_PROFILING
 1431            using (ProfileTimers.CreateTimedBlock("DiContainer.Inject"))
 1432#endif
 01433            {

 01435                {

 1437

 01442                        return;
 1443                    }

 01449                    }

 1453                        // at once
 1454                        try
 01455                        {
 01456                            InjectExplicitInternal(injectable, injectableType, extraArgs, context, concreteIdentifier);
 01457                        }
 01458                        catch (Exception e)
 01459                        {
 01460                            Log.ErrorException(e);
 01461                        }
 01462                    }
 01463                }
 1464                else
 01465                {
 01466                    InjectExplicitInternal(injectable, injectableType, extraArgs, context, concreteIdentifier);
 01467                }
 01468            }

 1471        void CallInjectMethodsTopDown(
 1472            object injectable, Type injectableType,
 1473            InjectTypeInfo typeInfo, List<TypeValuePair> extraArgs,
 1474            InjectContext context, object concreteIdentifier, bool isDryRun)
 01475        {
 01476            if (typeInfo.BaseTypeInfo != null)
 01477            {
 01478                CallInjectMethodsTopDown(
 1479                    injectable, injectableType, typeInfo.BaseTypeInfo, extraArgs,
 1480                    context, concreteIdentifier, isDryRun);
 01481            }
 1482
 01483            for (int i = 0; i < typeInfo.InjectMethods.Length; i++)
 01484            {
 01485                var method = typeInfo.InjectMethods[i];
 01486                var paramValues = ZenPools.SpawnArray<object>(method.Parameters.Length);
 1487
 1488                try
 01489                {
 01490                    for (int k = 0; k < method.Parameters.Length; k++)
 01491                    {
 01492                        var injectInfo = method.Parameters[k];
 1493
 1494                        object value;
 1495
 01496                        if (!InjectUtil.PopValueWithType(extraArgs, injectInfo.MemberType, out value))
 01497                        {
 01498                            using (var subContext = ZenPools.SpawnInjectContext(
 1499                                this, injectInfo, context, injectable, injectableType, concreteIdentifier))
 01500                            {
 01501                                value = Resolve(subContext);
 01502                            }
 01503                        }
 1504
 01505                        if (value is ValidationMarker)
 01506                        {
 01507                            Assert.That(IsValidating);
 1508
 01509                            paramValues[k] = injectInfo.MemberType.GetDefaultValue();
 01510                        }
 1511                        else
 01512                        {
 01513                            paramValues[k] = value;
 01514                        }
 01515                    }
 1516
 01517                    if (!isDryRun)
 01518                    {
 1519#if ZEN_INTERNAL_PROFILING
 1520                        using (ProfileTimers.CreateTimedBlock("User Code"))
 1521#endif
 1522#if UNITY_EDITOR
 01523                        using (ProfileBlock.Start("{0}.{1}()", typeInfo.Type, method.Name))
 1524#endif
 01525                        {
 01526                            method.Action(injectable, paramValues);
 01527                        }
 01528                    }
 01529                }
 1530                finally
 01531                {
 01532                    ZenPools.DespawnArray(paramValues);
 01533                }
 01534            }
 01535        }

 1537        void InjectMembersTopDown(
 1538            object injectable, Type injectableType,
 1539            InjectTypeInfo typeInfo, List<TypeValuePair> extraArgs,
 1540            InjectContext context, object concreteIdentifier, bool isDryRun)
 01541        {
 01542            if (typeInfo.BaseTypeInfo != null)
 01543            {
 01544                InjectMembersTopDown(
 1545                    injectable, injectableType, typeInfo.BaseTypeInfo, extraArgs,
 1546                    context, concreteIdentifier, isDryRun);
 01547            }
 1548
 01549            for (int i = 0; i < typeInfo.InjectMembers.Length; i++)
 01550            {
 01551                var injectInfo = typeInfo.InjectMembers[i].Info;
 01552                var setterMethod = typeInfo.InjectMembers[i].Setter;
 1553
 1554                object value;
 1555
 01556                if (InjectUtil.PopValueWithType(extraArgs, injectInfo.MemberType, out value))
 01557                {
 01558                    if (!isDryRun)
 01559                    {
 01560                        if (value is ValidationMarker)
 01561                        {
 01562                            Assert.That(IsValidating);
 01563                        }
 1564                        else
 01565                        {
 01566                            setterMethod(injectable, value);
 01567                        }
 01568                    }
 01569                }
 1570                else
 01571                {
 01572                    using (var subContext = ZenPools.SpawnInjectContext(
 1573                        this, injectInfo, context, injectable, injectableType, concreteIdentifier))
 01574                    {
 01575                        value = Resolve(subContext);
 01576                    }
 1577
 01578                    if (injectInfo.Optional && value == null)
 01579                    {
 1580                        // Do not override in this case so it retains the hard-coded value
 01581                    }
 1582                    else
 01583                    {
 01584                        if (!isDryRun)
 01585                        {
 01586                            if (value is ValidationMarker)
 01587                            {
 01588                                Assert.That(IsValidating);
 01589                            }
 1590                            else
 01591                            {
 01592                                setterMethod(injectable, value);
 01593                            }
 01594                        }
 01595                    }
 01596                }
 01597            }
 01598        }

 1816        Transform GetTransformGroup(
 1817            GameObjectCreationParameters gameObjectBindInfo, InjectContext context)
 01818        {
 01819            Assert.That(!AssertOnNewGameObjects,
 1820                "Given DiContainer does not support creating new game objects");
 1821
 01822            if (gameObjectBindInfo.ParentTransform != null)

 1828            }
 1829
 1830            // Don't execute the ParentTransformGetter method during validation
 1831            // since it might do a resolve etc.

 1841                        Container = this

 01843                }
 1844
 1845                // NOTE: Null is fine here, will just be a root game object in that case

 01849            var groupName = gameObjectBindInfo.GroupName;
 1850
 1851            // Only use the inherited parent if is not set locally

 01857                {

 01861                return (GameObject.Find("/" + groupName) ?? CreateTransformGroup(groupName)).transform;
 1862            }

 2283        // Inject dependencies into any and all child components on the given game object
 2284        public void InjectGameObject(GameObject gameObject)
 02285        {
 02286            FlushBindings();
 2287
 02288            ZenUtilInternal.AddStateMachineBehaviourAutoInjectersUnderGameObject(gameObject);
 2289
 02290            var monoBehaviours = ZenPools.SpawnList<MonoBehaviour>();
 2291            try
 02292            {
 02293                ZenUtilInternal.GetInjectableMonoBehavioursUnderGameObject(gameObject, monoBehaviours);
 2294
 02295                for (int i = 0; i < monoBehaviours.Count; i++)
 02296                {
 02297                    Inject(monoBehaviours[i]);
 02298                }
 02299            }
 2300            finally
 02301            {

 2633        // You shouldn't need to use this
 2634        public void FlushBindings()
 122635        {

 42637            {

 2639

 2641                    && binding.BindingInheritanceMethod != BindingInheritanceMethods.MoveIntoAll)

 02649                }
 2650                else

 2799        //    {

 2801        //
 2802        //    Container.BindInterfacesTo<Foo>().AsSingle();
 2803        //
 2804        //  This line above is equivalent to the following:
 2805        //
 2806        //    Container.Bind<ITickable>().ToSingle<Foo>();
 2807        //    Container.Bind<IInitializable>().ToSingle<Foo>();
 2808        //
 2809        // Note here that we do not bind Foo to itself.  For that, use BindInterfacesAndSelfTo
 2810        public FromBinderNonGeneric BindInterfacesTo<T>()
 02811        {
 02812            return BindInterfacesTo(typeof(T));
 02813        }
 2814
 2815        public FromBinderNonGeneric BindInterfacesTo(Type type)
 02816        {
 02817            var statement = StartBinding();
 02818            var bindInfo = statement.SpawnBindInfo();
 2819
 02820            var interfaces = type.Interfaces();
 2821
 02822            if (interfaces.Length == 0)
 02823            {
 02824                Log.Warn("Called BindInterfacesTo for type {0} but no interfaces were found", type);
 02825            }
 2826
 02827            bindInfo.ContractTypes.AllocFreeAddRange(interfaces);
 02828            bindInfo.SetContextInfo("BindInterfacesTo({0})".Fmt(type));
 2829
 2830            // Almost always, you don't want to use the default AsTransient so make them type it
 02831            bindInfo.RequireExplicitScope = true;
 02832            return BindInternal(bindInfo, statement).To(type);
 02833        }
 2834
 2835        // Same as BindInterfaces except also binds to self
 2836        public FromBinderNonGeneric BindInterfacesAndSelfTo<T>()
 02837        {
 02838            return BindInterfacesAndSelfTo(typeof(T));
 02839        }
 2840
 2841        public FromBinderNonGeneric BindInterfacesAndSelfTo(Type type)
 02842        {
 02843            var statement = StartBinding();
 02844            var bindInfo = statement.SpawnBindInfo();
 2845
 02846            bindInfo.ContractTypes.AllocFreeAddRange(type.Interfaces());
 02847            bindInfo.ContractTypes.Add(type);
 2848
 02849            bindInfo.SetContextInfo("BindInterfacesAndSelfTo({0})".Fmt(type));
 2850
 2851            // Almost always, you don't want to use the default AsTransient so make them type it
 02852            bindInfo.RequireExplicitScope = true;
 02853            return BindInternal(bindInfo, statement).To(type);
 02854        }
 2855
 2856        //  This is simply a shortcut to using the FromInstance method.
 2857        //
 2858        //  Example:
 2859        //      Container.BindInstance(new Foo());
 2860        //
 2861        //  This line above is equivalent to the following:
 2862        //
 2863        //      Container.Bind<Foo>().FromInstance(new Foo());
 2864        //
 2865        public IdScopeConcreteIdArgConditionCopyNonLazyBinder BindInstance<TContract>(TContract instance)
 02866        {
 02867            var statement = StartBinding();
 02868            var bindInfo = statement.SpawnBindInfo();
 02869            bindInfo.ContractTypes.Add(typeof(TContract));
 2870
 02871            statement.SetFinalizer(
 2872                new ScopableBindingFinalizer(
 2873                    bindInfo,
 2874                    (container, type) => new InstanceProvider(type, instance, container, bindInfo.InstantiatedCallback))
 2875
 02876            return new IdScopeConcreteIdArgConditionCopyNonLazyBinder(bindInfo);
 02877        }
 2878
 2879        // Unfortunately we can't support setting scope / condition / etc. here since all the
 2880        // bindings are finalized one at a time
 2881        public void BindInstances(params object[] instances)
 02882        {
 02883            for (int i = 0; i < instances.Length; i++)
 02884            {
 02885                var instance = instances[i];
 2886
 02887                Assert.That(!ZenUtilInternal.IsNull(instance),
 2888                    "Found null instance provided to BindInstances method");
 2889
 02890                Bind(instance.GetType()).FromInstance(instance);
 02891            }
 02892        }

 2955        MemoryPoolIdInitialSizeMaxSizeBinder<TItemContract> BindMemoryPoolCustomInterfaceInternal<TItemContract, TPoolCo
 2956            bool includeConcreteType, BindStatement statement)
 2957            where TPoolConcrete : TPoolContract, IMemoryPool
 2958            where TPoolContract : IMemoryPool
 02959        {
 02960            var contractTypes = new List<Type> { typeof(IDisposable), typeof(TPoolContract) };
 2961
 02962            if (includeConcreteType)
 02963            {
 02964                contractTypes.Add(typeof(TPoolConcrete));
 02965            }
 2966
 02967            var bindInfo = statement.SpawnBindInfo();
 2968
 02969            bindInfo.ContractTypes.AllocFreeAddRange(contractTypes);
 2970
 2971            // This interface is used in the optional class PoolCleanupChecker
 2972            // And also allow people to manually call DespawnAll() for all IMemoryPool
 2973            // if they want
 02974            bindInfo.ContractTypes.Add(typeof(IMemoryPool));
 2975
 02976            var factoryBindInfo = new FactoryBindInfo(typeof(TPoolConcrete));
 02977            var poolBindInfo = new MemoryPoolBindInfo();
 2978
 02979            statement.SetFinalizer(
 2980                new MemoryPoolBindingFinalizer<TItemContract>(
 2981                    bindInfo, factoryBindInfo, poolBindInfo));
 2982
 02983            return new MemoryPoolIdInitialSizeMaxSizeBinder<TItemContract>(
 2984                this, bindInfo, factoryBindInfo, poolBindInfo);
 02985        }
